Virtualization goes back to the 1960's and was made popular by VMWare in 1999 now it has morphed into a model that includes desktops, servers, networks, storage,
applications, and data devices. An Amazon IaaS example would EC2 (Amazon Compute Cloud) which provides vrtual servers. Virtualization allows them to run different 
types of machines on their hardware and it all can be controlled by a web interface.

